---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import TitleBar from "@components/TitleBar.astro";
import ContentBox from "@components/ContentBox.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <TitleBar title="Data Process" />
  <ContentBox title="Data Acquisition">
    <p class="p-1">
      Our dataset draws from three primary sources. The bulk of the data comes
      from <a class="underline text-primary" href="https://commoncrawl.org/"
        >Common Crawl</a
      >, specifically the <code>CC-MAIN-2026-04</code> archive from January 2026,
      which contains 2.30 billion web pages across roughly 70 TiB of data. Due to
      time and bandwidth constraints, we processed 10 TiB of that archive. To classify
      pages by topic, we used <a
        class="underline text-primary"
        href="https://newsapi.org/">NewsAPI</a
      > as a source of known news domains. To classify whether text was Al-generated,
      we used the
      <a
        class="underline text-primary"
        href="https://huggingface.co/fakespot-ai/roberta-base-ai-text-detection-v1"
        >fakespot-ai/roberta-base-ai-text-detection-v1</a
      > model from Hugging Face.
    </p>
  </ContentBox>

  <ContentBox title="Filtering">
    <p class="p-1">
      <!-- The main text of each page was extracted from raw HTML using
      <a
        class="underline text-primary"
        href="https://trafilatura.readthedocs.io/">Trafilatura</a
      >, and non-English pages were filtered out using
      <a
        class="underline text-primary"
        href="https://github.com/LlmKira/fast-langdetect">fast-langdetect</a
      >.  -->
      The main text of each page was extracted from raw HTML using Trafilatura, that
      means just visible text that actually counts as content. This excludes footer
      text for example. It is very similar to what what the firefox reader view does.
      We also removed all non-English pages using fast-langdetect. At first we tried
      not to but almost all of our remaining classification is much worse or not possible
      for other languages. Thus we decided to stick to an English subset of the data.
    </p>
  </ContentBox>

  <ContentBox title="Enrichment">
    <p class="p-1">
      We extracted 3 key feature from the filtered data. First we used the text
      with our AI Text Classification model to create a label "AI", "HUMAN",
      "UNSURE". Then we tokenized the text, extracting all words and lemmatizing
      them. We counted them up into a distribution per site. Finally we checked
      how many AI Companies or AI related keywords where in this distribution
      and labeled the data "AI TOPIC" and "NOT AI TOPIC". At last we looked at
      the url and determent by the domain if a site was a shop, news or other
      site. We also used other sources like NewsAPI, etc. for the topic
      classification in "NEWS", "SHOP", "BLOG" and "WIKI".
    </p>
  </ContentBox>

  <TitleBar title="Data Sources" />

  <ContentBox title="Common Crawl">
    <div class="p-1 grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
      <span class="font-medium">Format</span>
      <span
        >Raw WARC files (HTTP responses with headers and full page content)</span
      >
      <span class="font-medium">Output</span>
      <span>URL, HTTP headers, raw HTML body</span>
      <span class="font-medium">Purpose</span>
      <span
        >Bulk web page data from the <code>CC-MAIN-2026-04</code> archive (January
        2026)</span
      >
      <span class="font-medium">Link</span>
      <span
        ><a class="underline text-primary" href="https://commoncrawl.org/"
          >commoncrawl.org</a
        ></span
      >
    </div>
  </ContentBox>

  <ContentBox title="NewsAPI">
    <div class="p-1 grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
      <span class="font-medium">Format</span>
      <span
        >JSON (REST API, <code>/v2/top-headlines/sources</code> endpoint)</span
      >
      <span class="font-medium">Output</span>
      <span>URL</span>
      <span class="font-medium">Purpose</span>
      <span>Tag pages as news articles for topic-per-page classification</span>
      <span class="font-medium">Link</span>
      <span
        ><a class="underline text-primary" href="https://newsapi.org/"
          >newsapi.org</a
        ></span
      >
    </div>
  </ContentBox>

  <ContentBox title="Fakespot Al Detection Model">
    <div class="p-1 grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
      <span class="font-medium">Format</span>
      <span
        >Hugging Face model (<code
          >fakespot-ai/roberta-base-ai-text-detection-v1</code
        >, RoBERTa base)</span
      >
      <span class="font-medium">Output</span>
      <span><code>AI</code>, <code>HUMAN</code> labels</span>
      <span class="font-medium">Purpose</span>
      <span>Score each page's likelihood of being Al-generated</span>
      <span class="font-medium">Link</span>
      <span
        ><a
          class="underline text-primary"
          href="https://huggingface.co/fakespot-ai/roberta-base-ai-text-detection-v1"
          >Hugging Face</a
        ></span
      >
    </div>
  </ContentBox>
</Layout>
